	<section>

		<img src="images/p2pspsf.png" alt="P2PSP protocol" height="150" /><br />
		<ul>
			<li class="fragment">
				<h2><a href="http://www.p2psp.org/en/">P2PSP (Peer to Peer Straightforward Protocol)</a> is an open application-layer protocol for the real-time
			  	streaming of media content over a peer-to-peer overlay.</h2>
			</li>
			<br />
			<li class="fragment">	
				<h2>P2PSP is based on a push-based fully connected mesh scheme where every peer is connected with each other.</h2>
			</li>
			<br />
			<li class="fragment">
				<h2>An open-source (<a href="https://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html">GNU GPL v3</a>) implementation is available on <a href="https://github.com/p2psp">
			  	GitHub</a>.<br /><br />
				<center><a href="http://www.google-melange.com/gsoc/org2/google/gsoc2015/p2psp"><img src="images/gsoc.jpg" height="100px"/><br /><span style="font-size:x-large;"> P2PSP.org in Google Summer of Code </span></a></center>
				</h2>
			</li>
	    </ul>

	</section>

