	<section data-transition=none>
  		
		<h1>Strategy based on Trusted Peers.</h1><br />
		<h2><center>How does it work?</li></h2> <br />
		<img  src="images/strpe-2.svg" alt="STrPe" align="left" height="480" style="margin:5px"/> <br />
		<div><h3><b>1.</b> Only the splitter knows who the TPs in the team are.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>2.</b> Each TP creates a hash for each chunk, including the chunk number and the endpoint of the source and sends it to the splitter.</h3></div><br />
 	</section>
	<section data-transition=none>
  		
		<h1>Strategy based on Trusted Peers.</h1><br />
		<h2><center>How does it work?</li></h2> <br />
		<img  src="images/strpe-3.svg" alt="STrPe" align="left" height="480" style="margin:5px"/> <br />
		<div><h3><b>1.</b> Only the splitter knows who the TPs in the team are.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>2.</b> Each TP creates a hash for each chunk, including the chunk number and the endpoint of the source and sends it to the splitter.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>3.</b> The Splitter checks whether the chunks have been altered.</h3></div><br />
 	</section>
	<section data-transition=none>
  		
		<h1>Strategy based on Trusted Peers.</h1><br />
		<h2><center>How does it work?</li></h2> <br />
		<img  src="images/strpe-4.svg" alt="STrPe" align="left" height="480" style="margin:5px"/> <br />
		<div><h3><b>1.</b> Only the splitter knows who the TPs in the team are.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>2.</b> Each TP creates a hash for each chunk, including the chunk number and the endpoint of the source and sends it to the splitter.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>3.</b> The Splitter checks whether the chunks have been altered.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>4.</b> The splitter knows the peer in charge of relaying a given chunk.</h3></div><br />
 	</section>
	<section data-transition=none>
  		
		<h1>Strategy based on Trusted Peers.</h1><br />
		<h2><center>How does it work?</li></h2> <br />
		<img  src="images/strpe-5.svg" alt="STrPe" align="left" height="480" style="margin:5px"/> <br />
		<div><h3><b>1.</b> Only the splitter knows who the TPs in the team are.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>2.</b> Each TP creates a hash for each chunk, including the chunk number and the endpoint of the source and sends it to the splitter.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>3.</b> The Splitter checks whether the chunks have been altered.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>4.</b> The splitter knows the peer in charge of relaying a given chunk.</h3></div><br />
		<div><h3><b>5.</b> The attacker is expelled from the team.</h3></div><br />
 	</section>
	<!-- end of animation -->

	<section>

		<h1>Strategy based on Trusted Peers.</h1><br />
		<h2><center><b>Problems:</b></li></h2><br />
		<ul>
			<li class="fragment">
				<h2>Peers don't know if they are being poisoned.</h2>
			</li>
			<br />
			<li class="fragment">
				<h2>If an attacker knows who the trusted peers are the system is completely vulnerable to <span style="color:red;">Selective Attacks</span>.</h2>
			</li>
			<br />
	    </ul>

	</section>

